  "title": "Agentic AI Engineer (LangGraph & LLMs)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>·      We are looking for an Agentic AI Engineer to design, develop, and maintain scalable agentic AI workflows using LangGraph and Large Language Models (LLMs).</p><p>·       The role requires strong prompt engineering expertise, solid Python development skills, and hands-on experience working with Git-based CI/CD pipelines in a production environment.</p><p><strong> Key Responsibilities </strong></p><p>·      Design and develop reusable agentic AI workflows using LangGraph and LLMs Craft, test, and refine high-quality prompts to ensure reliable and consistent LLM outputs</p><p>·       Implement and understand Agent-to-Agent (A2A) orchestration patterns Write clean, production-ready Python code with comprehensive pytest unit tests.</p><p>·       Use Git for version control and collaborate within a team-based development environment.</p><p>·       Implement and maintain GitLab CI/CD pipelines for automated build, testing, and deployment.</p><p><strong> Required Skills</strong></p><p>·       Strong prompt engineering skills for LLM control and output reliability.</p><p>·       Proven experience with LangGraph, including building and maintaining reusable workflows and components.</p><p>·       Proficiency in Python, including writing and maintaining pytest-based unit tests .</p><p>·      Hands-on experience with Git and GitLab CI/CD pipelines.</p><p>·      <strong>Good-to-Have Skills:</strong>Hands-on experience in agentic AI system design and orchestration Solid understanding of Agent-to-Agent (A2A) orchestration principles</p>",
